MATLAB
-Matrix Laboratory
-High-level language for technical computing
-An easy-to-use environment where you can:
 >Compute
 >Visualize
 >Program
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Applications of MATLAB
-Graphics
-Algorithm Dev.
-Data acquisition and signal processing
 >Audio, speech, image, video, ECG, and EEG
-Data analysis
-Modelling and simulation
-GUI Modelling
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Variables in MATLAB
-variables can be
 >Scalar
 >Vector
 >Matrix
-No need to declare variables
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Naming Variables
-Can be 63 characters long
-Can contain letters, numbers, and underscores (MUST START WITH LETTER)
-Reserved words are not allowed to be used such as:
 >Pre-defined constants (eg: ans, pi, eps, inf, i/j, NaN, realmax, realmin)
 >Built-in functions
-Case-sensitive
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Operators in MATLAB
+ Addition
- Subtraction
* Multiplication
/ Scalar Division
^ Exponentiation
= Assignment Operator
.* Element-by-element Multiplication for Vectors and Matrices
./ Element-by-element Division for Vectors and Matrices
.^ Element-by-element Exponentiation for Vectors and Matrices
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Built-in Math commands

sin(x), cos(x), tan(x) etc. >Circular/Trigonometric Functinos in radians
sind(x), cosd(x), tand(x) >in degrees
sqrt(x) >Square root
exp(x) >Exponential function
log(x) >Natural logarithm
log10(x) >Common logarithm (base 10)
abs(x) >Modulus or magnitude of a complex variable (|Absoulute value|)
angle(x) >Argument or angle of a complex number
conj(x) >Conjugate
real(x) >Real part of a complex number
imag(x) >Imaginary part of a complex number
cart2sph() >Cartesian to Spherical coord
cart2pol() > Cartesian to polar coordinates
sph2cart() >Spherical to cartesian coordinates
pol2cart() >Polar to cartesian coordinates
fix(x) >Rounds toward zero
floor(x) >Rounds towards a lower integer
ceil(x) >Rounds towards a higher integer
round(x) >Rounds towards the nearest integer
primes(x) >All prime numbers less than x
gcd() >Greatest cmomon factor/divisor
lcm() >Least common multiple
rat() >Rational approximation
rats() >Rational form
rem() >Remainder after division
mod() >Modulo operation

eye(n) >Creates an anth order identity matrix
ones(m,n) >Creates an m x n matrix with all elements having a value of 1
rand(m,n) >Creates an m x n matrix with its elements uniformly distributed from 0 to 1
zeros(m,n) >Creates an m x n matrix with all elements having a value of 0
randn(m,n) >Creates an m x n matrix with Gaussian Distributed elements of zero mean and unit variance
magic(n) >Creates an n x n matrix where the sum of its diagonal, rows, and columns are equal
size(A) >Returns the dimensions of vector or matrix A
length(A) >Returns either the number of elements in vector A or max{m,n} pf ,atrox A whoes dimensions are m x n
sum(A) > Returns either the sums of either elements A 

sort(A) >Sorts each column of matrix A in ascending order
inv(A) >Inverse of matrix A
det(A) >Determinant of matrix A
rank(A) >Rank of matrix A
eig(A) >Eigenvalues of matrix A
norm(A) >Norm of vector or matrix A
transpose(A) >Transpose of matrix A
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Misc commands
- lookfor (keyword)
- help (keyword)
- clc - clears command window
- format <attribute> - Sets up the display format depending on the attribute placed after the format command
 FORMATTING ATTRIBUTE
 >short - scaled fixed point with 5 digits
 >long - format with 15 digits for double and 8 digits for single
 >short eng -Engineering notation that has at least 5 digits
 >long eng -engineering notation that has exactly 16 significant digits
 >hex - hexadecimal
 >rat - Approximation by ratio of small integers
